# ── Client env vars ──
# Vite reads these at BUILD time (not runtime). Every variable that needs to
# reach the browser must start with VITE_.
#
# For local dev: leave VITE_SERVER_URL unset — the client falls back to
# http://localhost:3001, which matches the default server port.
#
# For production: set this in your Vercel/Netlify dashboard to the public URL
# of your deployed server. Use https://, not http://, or browsers will block
# the WebSocket from a secure (https) page.
#
# Example: https://beatbattle-server.onrender.com

VITE_SERVER_URL=
